1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 24=

3
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,480
Talking work?

4
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,360
I came at a bad time, then.

5
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:46,960
Here for Gu Yan?

6
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,280
Sorry to intrude.

7
00:01:51,466 --> 00:01:52,733
I'll come back later.

8
00:02:08,866 --> 00:02:09,920
My wedding is in two days.

9
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,520
Zhou Mei agreed to be my bridesmaid.

10
00:02:11,688 --> 00:02:12,920
I hope you can make it, too.

11
00:02:13,511 --> 00:02:15,240
I know I always steal your resources

12
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:15,960
and your people.

13
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,960
But our rivalry kept me going.

14
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,800
Honestly, just thinking

15
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,750
that Colorful Culture Media
could beat Chenxing

16
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,400
is motivation.

17
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,960
You used to doubt Ling Yikai and me.

18
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,680
Now, I've proven you wrong.

19
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,560
I did it.

20
00:02:28,555 --> 00:02:29,533
Congratulations.

21
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,760
You made it.

22
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,480
I'll be there.

23
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:33,440
Thank you.

24
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:35,400
I have a question.

25
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:36,760
What is it?

26
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,720
Who is Sansan?

27
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,280
A new author I signed.

28
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:42,400
Is it Gu Yan?

29
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:43,720
No.

30
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:08,580
(Which of these books
and drafts do you want to keep?)

31
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:10,100
(I'll leave them at the front desk.)

32
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:11,460
(Otherwise, I'll get rid of them.)

33
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:25,920
Are you moving?

34
00:03:27,244 --> 00:03:28,280
It's not the first time.

35
00:03:28,755 --> 00:03:30,480
The best part about living in hotels is

36
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,600
that when you get sick of one,

37
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:32,760
you can just move to another.

38
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,680
Where are you moving?

39
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,680
Somewhere with a bit more culture.

40
00:03:40,177 --> 00:03:41,480
I'll come see you after work.

41
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,520
Wait for me.

42
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:05,140
(Tianyi Games: About Us)

43
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,000
Sorry for making you all work overtime.

44
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:14,610
Hello.

45
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:15,020
- Ms. Lin.
- Ms. Lin.

46
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:15,450
It's no problem.

47
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,755
I just explained
the situation to the team.

48
00:04:18,022 --> 00:04:19,640
They're playing hardball, so be ready.

49
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,520
Let's get started, then.

50
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:22,160
Okay.

51
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:22,480
Okay.

52
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,760
Tianyi Games

53
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,560
has developed many projects

54
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:29,200
since its founding in 2015.

55
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,800
Take "Wildfire",

56
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,480
a major game they made years ago.

57
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,400
It's still a hit.

58
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,760
I'm sure you all know it.

59
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,200
Their founder, Mr. Kun,

60
00:04:37,266 --> 00:04:39,488
(Kun Zhida)
is actually a fan of He Han's work.

61
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,720
Two years ago,

62
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:41,955
they approached us about

63
00:04:42,022 --> 00:04:44,640
the adaptation rights
for "Tao Yao: Dream of Wuchuan".

64
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,960
But their proposal failed to

65
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,960
capture the essence of the novel,

66
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,960
so the deal fell through.

67
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:52,880
So now,

68
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,800
they're basically
reviving an old proposal.

69
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,760
The most infuriating part is

70
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:57,640
that the proposal is

71
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,990
the same as it was two years ago.

72
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,280
They didn't even
bother changing the date.

73
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,800
They just lowered the licensing fee.

74
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,760
Kicking us while we're down.

75
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,440
Mr. Kun claims

76
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:09,440
he has a last-minute trip next week.

77
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:11,080
So he can only see us tomorrow,

78
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,200
and only for two hours in the afternoon.

79
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,280
How else would he show off

80
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,600
how much money he makes?

81
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,120
True.

82
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,440
It's a compliance test.

83
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,960
By sitting here today,

84
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,000
we've already started the negotiation.

85
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,840
He's trying to gain the upper hand

86
00:05:26,888 --> 00:05:28,000
to make us back down.

87
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,680
Our goal today

88
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,520
is to establish our bottom line

89
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,044
and devise a counter-strategy.

90
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:46,880
Mr. He.

91
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,120
Sorry to bother you.

92
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,040
It's okay. Come in.

93
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,000
Would you mind

94
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,360
settling this bill?

95
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,880
Your previous balance

96
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:55,977
has already been cleared,

97
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,000
and the deposit was refunded.

98
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,680
The invoice was sent to your email.

99
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,844
So for this extra charge...

100
00:06:00,866 --> 00:06:01,733
No problem.

101
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,200
I'm really sorry for the trouble.

102
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,440
Don't be sorry.

103
00:06:05,511 --> 00:06:07,480
I should be thanking you
for taking care of me.

104
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,400
It's my pleasure.

105
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:09,880
Hold on.

106
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,080
A sponsor gave me this model sports car.

107
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,000
I think your son might like it.

108
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:22,320
Mr. He, this is too generous.

109
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,640
I can't accept it.

110
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,488
Please, take it.

111
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,560
Do you need anything else, Mr. He?

112
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:28,920
Like packing or booking a car...

113
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,000
- Or...
- No, I'm good.

114
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,760
Alright. I'll see you off tomorrow.

115
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:33,560
Never mind.

116
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,120
You see off so many guests every day.

117
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,240
One less won't matter.

118
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:37,360
Understood, Mr. He.

119
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,844
- Go back to work.
- I'll get going.

120
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,400
Here we go.

121
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,440
Food's here.

122
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,680
Pass it around.

123
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,160
Even though we're working late,

124
00:06:59,280 --> 00:06:59,920
we still need

125
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,640
to keep our nutrition up.

126
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,600
Here, pass this.

127
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:02,960
Thanks.

128
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,400
- Get some Vitamin C.
- Thanks.

129
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:04,680
Here.

130
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,200
- Come on. Help yourselves.
- Vitamin C.

131
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,000
Come on.

132
00:07:07,377 --> 00:07:08,600
- Thanks.
- This is for you.

133
00:07:08,888 --> 00:07:10,200
Eat first. I'm not hungry.

134
00:07:10,688 --> 00:07:12,320
Ms. Lin, you have dinner plans tonight?

135
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,760
Look at the time.
More like a midnight snack.

136
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,280
Just eat your food.

137
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,000
Now,

138
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,680
I'll walk you through it while you eat.

139
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,000
Adapting supporting characters is fine.

140
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:26,000
But the main characters must follow

141
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,480
our character bios.

142
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:30,400
The style is still based on

143
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,760
"Wildfire".

144
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,280
Because that's his comfort zone.

145
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,000
But to us,

146
00:07:35,066 --> 00:07:36,320
it feels like a forced mashup.

147
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,480
Ms. Lin,

148
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,840
isn't he a fan of He Han?

149
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,760
Why is he demanding such big changes?

150
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,440
Fundamentally, I think

151
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:43,960
what he really wants to make

152
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,280
is "Tao Yao of Wildfire."

153
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,480
So he wants to force his personal mark

154
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,600
onto "Tao Yao: Dream of Wuchuan."

155
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,840
Mr. Kun's assistant just messaged.

156
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,920
They asked the Chenxing team

157
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,800
to do some homework
before tomorrow's meeting

158
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,800
and familiarize ourselves
with "Wildfire."

159
00:07:58,844 --> 00:08:00,333
Here's the intro for "Wildfire."

160
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,133
Should I cast it?

161
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,120
Yes.

162
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,400
Put it up. Let's see.

163
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,320
They also want us to focus

164
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,520
on the player comments section.

165
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:37,640
It's right here.

166
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,440
This includes feedback on characters,

167
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,560
plotlines, and level design.

168
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,955
They want us to read through it.

169
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,040
They want us to...

170
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,320
Did they send this, too?

171
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,280
Mr. Kun wants us

172
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,200
to see

173
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,760
their status among players

174
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,000
and understand their strengths.

175
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,760
Pure narcissism.

176
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,355
Come in half an hour early tomorrow.

177
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,200
Thanks, everyone.

178
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:34,920
Got it, Ms. Lin.

179
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,000
- Got it.
- Okay, Ms. Lin.

180
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,320
At your hotel in five minutes.

181
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:15,800
Hello, Miss.

182
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,720
How can I help you?

183
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:17,760
Hi, where is Mr. He?

184
00:12:18,066 --> 00:12:18,977
He checked out.

185
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,488
He left a few minutes ago.

186
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,240
Hello, Ms. Lin.

187
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,680
Mr. He left this for you.

188
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,760
Are you taking it all?

189
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,111
I'll take it all. Thanks.

190
00:12:32,177 --> 00:12:32,577
Okay.

191
00:12:32,644 --> 00:12:34,670
♪For first love♪

192
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,700
(You've retracted a message.)

193
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:41,700
(He Han)

194
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:45,690
♪It was a constant pursuit♪

195
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:51,240
♪Yet no one ever knew♪

196
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:56,870
♪For so long♪

197
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:02,770
♪I longed to be with you♪

198
00:13:04,370 --> 00:13:07,950
♪And you finally appeared♪

199
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:13,400
♪Calling my name in the air♪

200
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:19,100
♪Waiting with open arms♪

201
00:13:20,930 --> 00:13:24,380
♪I see you at the end♪

202
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:30,110
♪Now I cross the line♪

203
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:31,360
Sent.

204
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:36,250
♪Just to love and be with you♪

205
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,360
Discarded a five, and drew a six.

206
00:13:49,355 --> 00:13:52,066
♪Now I cross the line♪

207
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:57,950
♪Just to love and be with you♪

208
00:13:59,711 --> 00:14:01,288
♪Love♪

209
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:09,111
♪Cause now I see you there♪

210
00:14:10,488 --> 00:14:14,977
♪Waiting with open arms♪

211
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:20,422
♪I see you at the end♪

212
00:14:21,711 --> 00:14:25,600
♪Now I cross the line♪

213
00:14:26,288 --> 00:14:31,666
♪Just to love and be with you♪

214
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:47,511
♪Now I cross the line♪

215
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:53,888
♪Just to love and be with you♪

216
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:18,330
♪Call my name♪

217
00:15:18,444 --> 00:15:20,977
♪Here we are♪

218
00:15:21,711 --> 00:15:26,155
♪I'm waiting for long♪

219
00:15:26,644 --> 00:15:29,510
♪Stay where you are♪

220
00:15:29,510 --> 00:15:32,288
♪I will come to you♪

221
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:36,577
♪I'll never let you go♪

222
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,040
Are you asleep?

223
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,680
I'm downstairs.

224
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:15,880
Hello?

225
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,120
Why are you here so late?

226
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,120
Nothing.

227
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,000
I met up with a friend.

228
00:16:26,577 --> 00:16:27,866
I didn't want to go home,

229
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,640
so I came to see you.

230
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,280
It's late.

231
00:16:58,840 --> 00:16:59,960
Did I disturb you?

232
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:02,360
It's fine.

233
00:17:03,177 --> 00:17:04,488
I was replying to emails.

234
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,760
About the divorce...

235
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:10,360
I've brought it up with my wife.

236
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:14,360
I'm not joking around.

237
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:16,480
And it's not on a whim.

238
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,920
I've been waiting for the right moment.

239
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,240
And this seems like the best time.

240
00:17:24,022 --> 00:17:25,866
When things are going badly for me,

241
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,840
proposing to split our assets

242
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,280
might be easier for her to accept.

243
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:34,640
What did she say?

244
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:37,880
Shocked.

245
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:39,480
Surprised.

246
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,280
She needs time to process it.

247
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:49,960
Give me a little more time.

248
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:50,680
Okay?

249
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:52,960
It won't be long.

250
00:17:54,444 --> 00:17:55,640
Mrs. Bei was worried

251
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:58,022
that Lawyer Bei might
get dragged into other messes.

252
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,400
Using asset planning as an excuse,

253
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:01,960
she asked Lawyer Bei for a divorce.

254
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,840
In every possible way,

255
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,080
Lawyer Bei is against it.

256
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,040
But it's hard to save yourself.

257
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:10,960
Even for lawyers.

258
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,080
Mrs. Bei didn't do this on a whim.

259
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,560
She came prepared.

260
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,840
A model couple in public,

261
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:20,800
but behind closed doors,

262
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,520
only they know the truth.

263
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:33,760
Why are you smiling?

264
00:18:36,977 --> 00:18:38,240
Because life is unpredictable.

265
00:18:50,955 --> 00:18:52,760
Has Zhang Yousen looked for you lately?

266
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:53,800
No.

267
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,120
Are you new here?

268
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,160
Come here.

269
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,720
Sir, what do you do?

270
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,200
I'm the king of stories.

271
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:46,680
What about you?

272
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,640
Jun, you're going to be late for school!

273
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:54,880
For you.

274
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:03,440
Bye, Sir.

275
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:28,880
Heading out?

276
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:03,140
(Zhanqiao: Where did you move to?)

277
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,560
Hello, Mr. Kun.

278
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,520
Lin Zhanqiao.

279
00:21:13,533 --> 00:21:14,040
After you.

280
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:15,320
How are you still in this dump?

281
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,422
The same shabby storefront.

282
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:20,360
Fix it.

283
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:22,360
If we work together,

284
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:23,200
my first task

285
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,800
will be to expand this office for you.

286
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,040
Or we could move it.

287
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:28,440
How about that?

288
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:30,133
Hello, Mr. Kun.

289
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,040
Mantou, take Mr. Kun inside.

290
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,680
I need to take this call. Sorry.

291
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:35,880
This way, Mr. Kun.

292
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:36,920
Right this way.

293
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:37,480
Hello, Mr. Kun.

294
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,120
Please, come in.

295
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:38,760
This way.

296
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:39,440
Please.

297
00:21:39,466 --> 00:21:40,280
- Have a seat.
- Hello?

298
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:41,120
Right this way.

299
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:43,640
Did you get the books?

300
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:45,320
Where did you move to?

301
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,520
Send me your address.

302
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,280
I need to see you about something.

303
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:52,200
Okay.

304
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,880
What you just pitched

305
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,600
is how you handle online fiction.

306
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:58,920
Games have their own rules.

307
00:21:59,400 --> 00:21:59,880
Understand?

308
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,520
My last game had

309
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,320
over 100 million downloads.

310
00:22:06,044 --> 00:22:07,911
Hundreds of millions in monthly traffic.

311
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:09,640
Can you do that?

312
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:10,640
Who?

313
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,155
Your best online fiction,

314
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:16,640
even He Han's novel...

315
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,360
How big of an audience can you reach?

316
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:19,760
How big?

317
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,360
We are in completely different leagues.

318
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,520
Understand?

319
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,760
I want to buy
"Tao Yao: Dream of Wuchuan".

320
00:22:28,577 --> 00:22:30,360
And the only reason
I'm here talking to you

321
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,680
is that I'm a loyal fan of He Han.

322
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,377
Understand?

323
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,760
I know exactly how to turn his story

324
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,800
into a better game.

325
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,200
You guys don't.

326
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,120
You don't know.

327
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:43,040
You don't know.

328
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,577
Lin Zhanqiao certainly doesn't know.

329
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,400
Don't you guys need money?

330
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:49,680
Our company has plenty of it.

331
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:51,720
Take the money.

332
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,960
Then, stay out of the rest.

333
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,640
Mr. Kun

334
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,120
is impossible to talk to.

335
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,440
What he wants is

336
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:14,040
a co-branded game with He Han.

337
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,960
And at the same time,
erase our involvement entirely.

338
00:23:20,177 --> 00:23:21,480
Let's wait and see for now.

339
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,720
Unless we're out of options,

340
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:26,160
we need to keep our pride.

341
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,200
Should I take you back now?

342
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:31,800
Actually...

343
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:35,480
Drop me off at Siwei Apartments.

344
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:36,560
Okay.

345
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:37,444
Siwei Apartments.

346
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:52,680
Ms. Lin.

347
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:53,760
Come in.

348
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:01,720
Tell me.

349
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:02,760
Why are you here?

350
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,120
Or did you just want to soak in

351
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,280
the cultural atmosphere here?

352
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:26,000
I wanted to ask you

353
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:29,120
about your future plans.

354
00:25:31,466 --> 00:25:32,360
I haven't decided.

355
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,600
Need a drink?

356
00:25:44,066 --> 00:25:45,311
I'm ordering delivery.

357
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:46,240
I'm good.

358
00:25:46,822 --> 00:25:47,955
Just order for yourself.

359
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,080
Two Americanos.

360
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:09,960
Things aren't going well on my end.

361
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:19,840
A shortage of new authors?

362
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:21,520
There's no one we can use.

363
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:24,880
What about your pillar,

364
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:25,920
Gu Yan?

365
00:26:26,155 --> 00:26:27,560
What if I told you that Sansan,

366
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,577
who's writing the sequel

367
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:31,920
to "Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,"
is actually Gu Yan?

368
00:26:44,266 --> 00:26:45,440
It's a breach of contract.

369
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,200
I don't have proof.

370
00:26:48,444 --> 00:26:50,360
I believe Zhao Lanxin
already talked to him.

371
00:26:52,177 --> 00:26:53,480
So the contract and payments

372
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:55,240
are routed through someone else.

373
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:57,600
But why? Just for the money?

374
00:27:00,177 --> 00:27:01,440
Probably a lack of security.

375
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:05,480
His debut was late,

376
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,440
and you've
overshadowed him as a legend.

377
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,640
That has nothing to do with me.

378
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,560
Maybe you didn't
give him enough security.

379
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:16,760
Maybe he feels

380
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:18,520
that if he ever became useless,

381
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:19,640
you'd just toss him aside.

382
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,440
So he had to find a backup plan.

383
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:22,920
He had to

384
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,760
prove he's better than everyone else.

385
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,360
Can Zhao Lanxin give him security?

386
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:27,700
He doesn't care about Zhao Lanxin.

387
00:27:27,710 --> 00:27:28,680
Security isn't an issue.

388
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:38,960
"Parting with Yan Dan
at Yishui" by Sansan

389
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,440
is currently ranking higher

390
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:44,160
most of the time

391
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:46,240
than Gu Yan's own work,

392
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:47,520
"Drunk Old Friend."

393
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,480
I can understand why.

394
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,880
It's probably due to

395
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:53,866
- the Phantom Knight's hype.
- Lin Zhanqiao.

396
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:57,880
What are you trying to say?

397
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,080
I want you back at Chenxing.

398
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:18,560
I can't.

399
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,400
I really can't find a better author.

400
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:24,040
I need you back.

401
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,080
We can develop a new project together.

402
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:26,480
And then,

403
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,320
I'll talk to Mr. Fan.

404
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,360
What project?

405
00:28:29,577 --> 00:28:31,000
I haven't figured it out yet.

406
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:34,560
When will you?

407
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:40,360
I don't think staying here alone

408
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,440
will change anything.

409
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:43,080
What are you running from?

410
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:45,360
Dai Shan is gone.

411
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,000
Things are tense
between you and Mr. Fan.

412
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:47,800
You need someone

413
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,400
to help you handle the fallout,

414
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,000
so you can fully focus

415
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,480
on a new project, right?

416
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,680
So you want me back at Chenxing

417
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:56,200
because you think I still need you.

418
00:28:56,666 --> 00:28:57,960
Your life and your writing

419
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:59,680
have hit a major bottleneck.

420
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,560
You aren't a god.

421
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:03,120
Why won't you admit it?

422
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:05,200
You're just like everyone else.

423
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,920
Everyone goes through rough patches.

424
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:09,040
There's no shame in admitting it.

425
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,440
Accepting help from others isn't...

426
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:11,960
Thanks for the gesture, Lin Zhanqiao.

427
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,000
But I don't need it.

428
00:29:16,377 --> 00:29:17,480
You just said it yourself.

429
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,680
The company has so many issues.

430
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,800
It's overwhelming.

431
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,760
So don't let me add to your burden.

432
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:27,600
Let's handle our own problems.

433
00:29:36,355 --> 00:29:37,680
Hello. Your delivery is here.

434
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:11,400
I hope you can do as you said

435
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:16,440
and actually solve your own problems.

436
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:17,777
When that time comes,

437
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:19,600
I'll buy you that coffee.

438
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:10,440
Hello?

439
00:31:10,933 --> 00:31:11,840
Are you sleeping?

440
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,720
I'm picking up my parents now

441
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,240
to take them to their hotel.

442
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:19,240
Tomorrow morning,
I'll pick up your grandma.

443
00:31:19,488 --> 00:31:20,560
Makeup starts at 8:30 AM.

444
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,120
Get here around 9:00 AM.

445
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,160
Don't be late.

446
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:32,360
Mei.

447
00:31:33,244 --> 00:31:35,911
Are you going to Zhao Lanxin's hotel
first thing tomorrow?

448
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:38,120
Yeah, I'm her bridesmaid.

449
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:41,600
So her best friend is actually you?

450
00:31:43,088 --> 00:31:44,720
She doesn't have any other friends.

451
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,640
She's always alone.

452
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,280
Once she's married, she won't be.

453
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,360
On the surface, sure.

454
00:31:52,480 --> 00:31:53,200
But in reality,

455
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:54,520
she's still alone.

456
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:01,300
(Lift)

457
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:01,880
Let's go, Mom.

458
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,240
I've booked your rooms.

459
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,240
We can head straight up from the garage.

460
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:08,320
One room each.

461
00:32:08,422 --> 00:32:09,488
Next door to each other.

462
00:32:10,044 --> 00:32:10,880
Next door is good.

463
00:32:11,870 --> 00:32:12,410
Yes.

464
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:13,880
This way.

465
00:32:17,760 --> 00:32:18,920
Dad, this room is yours.

466
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:19,720
Okay.

467
00:32:21,711 --> 00:32:22,840
Mom, yours is next door.

468
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:23,400
Alright.

469
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:24,440
Get some rest.

470
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,360
Here, this one is yours.

471
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:29,800
Is your bridal suite here, too?

472
00:32:30,244 --> 00:32:31,622
It's at the end of the hall.

473
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:34,600
Are you staying here tonight?

474
00:32:35,155 --> 00:32:37,400
It was decorated this afternoon.
I'll leave it as is.

475
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:38,800
Head back, then.

476
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:39,720
Get some rest.

477
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:40,040
Okay.

478
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:44,400
Good night.

479
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:19,200
Mom.

480
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:20,160
Ready?

481
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:21,520
Yes, I'm ready.

482
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,440
Lanxin, when is breakfast?

483
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,000
- I'm starving.
- Right now.

484
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:27,111
Let's wait for Dad.

485
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:29,450
- What is it?
- Let's go.

486
00:33:29,450 --> 00:33:29,920
Hurry up.

487
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:30,790
- Time for breakfast.
- Already?

488
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:31,560
I haven't shaved yet.

489
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:31,990
It's fine.

490
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,280
Do it when we come back up.

491
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:33,977
- Okay.
- Yeah.

492
00:33:43,044 --> 00:33:44,440
The buffet is on the fourth floor.

493
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,840
Give them your room number.

494
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:46,280
Okay.

495
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:46,880
Alright.

496
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:49,022
You guys go eat.
I'll head back to the suite.

497
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,280
Hello, Zhou Mei.

498
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:14,000
You're here?

499
00:34:14,355 --> 00:34:15,977
Okay, I'll come down and get you.

500
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:32,740
(Mengtong Internet Cafe)

501
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:33,955
- Two boxes, right?
- Yes.

502
00:34:34,044 --> 00:34:34,879
Heading to work?

503
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:35,240
Yeah.

504
00:34:36,533 --> 00:34:37,870
Check this food order.

505
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:38,400
Alright.

506
00:34:38,911 --> 00:34:39,640
I'm taking off.

507
00:34:39,640 --> 00:34:40,080
Thanks.

508
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:41,244
Take care.

509
00:34:58,880 --> 00:34:59,640
Why are you here?

510
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:02,000
I need to show you something.

511
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,720
I don't need anything.

512
00:35:04,044 --> 00:35:05,360
I'm already making adjustments.

513
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:07,000
We'll talk once I finish writing.

514
00:35:08,044 --> 00:35:09,711
It's not about "Drunk Old Friend".

515
00:35:10,822 --> 00:35:11,777
Then what is it?

516
00:35:12,688 --> 00:35:14,244
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui".

517
00:35:15,644 --> 00:35:17,888
Even though
Phantom Knight didn't finish it,

518
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:22,120
authors always like to prepare
their character bios and outlines.

519
00:35:22,533 --> 00:35:25,333
(2019 "Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui")
They even establish the lore in advance.

520
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,340
("Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"
Project Plan)

521
00:35:28,100 --> 00:35:35,140
(Ten Hours Ago)

522
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:47,360
Hello?

523
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:49,240
About Gu Yan ghostwriting for Sansan,

524
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,320
I thought of a way

525
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:51,520
to give him a warning.

526
00:35:52,244 --> 00:35:54,377
The synopsis and world-building
of Phantom Knight's

527
00:35:54,840 --> 00:35:56,480
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"

528
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:57,640
are with you.

529
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:20,740
(2019 0818 "Parting with Yan Dan
at Yishui" Plot Outline)

530
00:36:20,740 --> 00:36:21,860
("Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"
Project Plan)

531
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:22,820
(Author: Phantom Knight.
Editor in Charge: Ma Zi'ang)

532
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,440
These files are from 2019.

533
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:25,960
Are you saying

534
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:27,840
Phantom Knight finished it long ago?

535
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:29,200
Believe it or not.

536
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,560
How did you get this?

537
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:33,960
Coincidence.

538
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,240
You're Phantom Knight?

539
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:44,120
Mr. Fan said

540
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:47,080
you started out writing novels

541
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,600
before switching to editing.

542
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:52,800
I can't believe
you're actually Phantom Knight.

543
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:55,240
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

544
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,200
And since the synopsis for

545
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:58,888
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"
was done,

546
00:36:58,955 --> 00:37:00,066
why did you stop writing?

547
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:06,880
So you are Sansan.

548
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:10,920
I'm not.

549
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:14,440
Then, I'm not Phantom Knight.

550
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:16,480
Why give this to me?

551
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:18,600
If you aren't Sansan,

552
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,320
or you don't know him,

553
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,960
then after reading this synopsis,

554
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:25,120
just treat it as light reading.

555
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:27,560
But if you are Sansan,

556
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,000
to cover your tracks

557
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,320
and keep me from suspecting you,

558
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:34,160
after reading this,

559
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,400
unless you can write
something even better,

560
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,160
you'll have to forget it to avoid

561
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:39,920
similarities.

562
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:43,400
But for you,

563
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:46,880
that won't be easy.

564
00:37:52,120 --> 00:37:52,720
Take your time.

565
00:37:53,822 --> 00:37:55,440
I'm going to Zhao Lanxin's wedding.

566
00:38:07,940 --> 00:38:11,260
(2019 "Parting with Yan Dan
at Yishui" Lore)

567
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:12,120
This way.

568
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:17,160
The watch

569
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:18,400
is in the car.

570
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:19,800
I'll get it.

571
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:20,560
Okay.

572
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,080
Ling Yikai.

573
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:48,000
Ling Yikai.

574
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:54,560
Ling Yikai.

575
00:39:15,320 --> 00:39:16,040
Ling Yikai!

576
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:18,200
Who is it?

577
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:23,800
Get dressed and get out.

578
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:26,840
You're early.

579
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:38,840
No rush.

580
00:40:01,666 --> 00:40:02,600
What do you want?

581
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,480
I should be asking you.
What do you want?

582
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:06,240
Are you mad?

583
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:15,480
Of course you are.

584
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:19,480
It's our wedding day.

585
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:22,240
And this is our bridal suite.

586
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:24,960
Yet you walk in on me

587
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,222
while I'm in bed with her.

588
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:28,511
You did it on purpose?

589
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,840
I wouldn't call it intentional.

590
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:32,640
I've always been like this.

591
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,120
You know that.

592
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,880
It's not too late to back out.

593
00:40:37,720 --> 00:40:39,000
You don't have to marry me.

594
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,080
Save yourself.

595
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:47,280
You just want to gross me out,

596
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:48,733
hoping I can't stomach it

597
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:49,960
and let you go?

598
00:40:51,022 --> 00:40:51,840
Keep dreaming.

599
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:55,240
Today is my big day.

600
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,480
No one is going to ruin it.

601
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,444
Not even you, Ling Yikai.

602
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,120
Why force this?

603
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,520
Must we both lose?

604
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:05,000
Do you think

605
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,360
living every day at each other's throats

606
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:07,990
is sustainable?

607
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,760
First, I haven't lost.

608
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:11,040
Second,

609
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:13,200
who doesn't
grit their teeth through life?

610
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,560
So,

611
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:15,880
I will make sure

612
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:17,533
everything goes according to my plan.

613
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:20,200
Are you insane?

614
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:22,360
Judging by this morning,

615
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:23,240
you're the insane one.

616
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:24,360
You drove me to it.

617
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,800
Everyone sees how good I am to you.

618
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:30,520
I gave up my career
and sold my house for you.

619
00:41:30,520 --> 00:41:31,911
I took care of your grandmother.

620
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:33,760
And on our wedding day,

621
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,688
I have to endure your
cheating and betrayal.

622
00:41:45,520 --> 00:41:46,760
I'll give you two choices.

623
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:47,880
You either leave now,

624
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:49,440
or stay for the banquet.

625
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:50,666
I'll save you a seat.

626
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,520
Are you insane?

627
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:05,440
Ling Yikai.

628
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,760
I'm taking my parents to get changed

629
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:09,520
before the videographer arrives.

630
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:12,000
Go take a shower
and scrub yourself clean.

631
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:13,880
Put on your suit.

632
00:42:14,933 --> 00:42:16,911
Once my makeup is done
and my dress is on,

633
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:18,080
we serve tea

634
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:20,200
to my parents and your grandmother.

635
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:26,440
Happy wedding day.

636
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

637
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

638
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

639
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

640
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

641
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

642
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

643
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

644
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

645
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

646
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

647
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

648
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

649
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

650
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

651
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

652
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

653
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

654
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

655
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

656
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

657
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

658
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

659
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

660
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

661
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

662
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

663
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

664
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

665
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

666
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

667
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

668
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

669
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

670
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

671
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

672
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
